From: Loc Ho <lho@apm.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Jul 2017 11:24:37 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] ACPI: APEI: Enable APEI multiple GHES source to share a
 single external IRQ

Git-commit: bdb9458a3382ba745a66be5526d3899103c76eda
Patch-mainline: Queued
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/next/linux-next.git
References: bsc#1053627

X-Gene platforms describe multiple GHES error sources with the same
hardware error notification type (external interrupt) and interrupt
number.

Change the GHES interrupt request to support sharing the same IRQ.

This change includs contributions from Tuan Phan <tphan@apm.com>.

Signed-off-by: Loc Ho <lho@apm.com>
Acked-by: Borislav Petkov <bp@suse.de>
Signed-off-by: Rafael J. Wysocki <rafael.j.wysocki@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Mian Yousaf Kaukab <yousaf.kaukab@suse.com>
---
 drivers/acpi/apei/ghes.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/acpi/apei/ghes.c b/drivers/acpi/apei/ghes.c
index 86ef89bcfbbd..4da6c771ede0 100644
--- a/drivers/acpi/apei/ghes.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/apei/ghes.c
@@ -1012,7 +1012,8 @@ static int ghes_probe(struct platform_device *ghes_dev)
 			       generic->header.source_id);
 			goto err_edac_unreg;
 		}
-		rc = request_irq(ghes->irq, ghes_irq_func, 0, "GHES IRQ", ghes);
+		rc = request_irq(ghes->irq, ghes_irq_func, IRQF_SHARED,
+				 "GHES IRQ", ghes);
 		if (rc) {
 			pr_err(GHES_PFX "Failed to register IRQ for generic hardware error source: %d\n",
 			       generic->header.source_id);
